<p>In December 2025, our Mexico team came together to support their local community in a very real way. They organized a fundraiser to prepare and serve meals for patients and families at Querétaro General Hospital during the Christmas season.</p>

<h2>155 tortas, and a lot of care</h2>
<p>The team prepared 155 tortas, a classic Mexican-style sandwich, along with juice and water. Simple, filling, and comforting. For many people spending the holidays in a hospital, a fresh meal like that can lift the day more than you might expect.</p>
<p>This was not a big corporate production. The team handled the fundraising, prep, and delivery themselves. It showed how much impact a committed group can have when they decide to step up for their community.</p>
<p>We are incredibly proud of the Mexico team for turning compassion into action and reminding all of us that giving back does not have to be complicated. Sometimes it just takes good food, some time, and the willingness to care.</p>
